quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  109,1,"Say: “O unbelievers!”",footnotes:182871:1
  109,2,"I do not worship those that you worship",footnotes:182872:1
  109,3,"neither do you worship Him Whom I worship;",footnotes:182873:1
  109,4,"nor will I worship those whom you have worshipped;"
  109,5,"nor are you going to worship Him Whom I worship.",footnotes:182874:1
  109,6,"To you is your religion, and to me, my religion.",footnotes:182875:1
  110,1,"When the help comes from Allah, and victory (is granted),",footnotes:182876:1
  110,2,"and you see people entering Allah's religion in multitudes,",footnotes:182877:1
  110,3,"then extol the praise of your Lord and pray to Him for forgiveness. For He indeed is ever disposed to accept repentance.",footnotes:182878:1,footnotes:182879:2
  111,1,"Destroyed were the hands of Abu Lahab, and he lay utterly doomed.",footnotes:182880:1
  111,2,"His wealth did not avail him, nor his acquisitions.",footnotes:182881:1
  111,3,"Surely, he will be cast into a Flaming Fire"
  111,4,"along with his wife, that carrier of slanderous tales;",footnotes:182882:1,footnotes:182883:2
  111,5,"upon her neck shall be a rope of palm-fibre.",footnotes:182884:1